<br>
The golden lioness glanced around at those gathered.  Her eyes seeking out Artemis, but she was not to be found.   It had become time for Artemis to prove herself more then the Goddess of the Hunt.  Making a mark for herself and her legend as the known Goddess of the Amazons.  <br>
<br>
Relaxing as she watched, the lioness's lower jaw dropped to breath heavy the warm humid air of the island.  The scent of burning flesh would have normally brought the lioness into a feeding frenzy.  But, this flesh was not of mortal kind.  Lifting her nose to the air, Sin then quickly blew out the evil scent in a snort. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/14/02 11:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Golden eyes in the flames</span><hr size=1> ~ In a smal burstof silver flames, Artemis arrived in her own amazon leathers. If you could call it that. A Silver halter and silver skirt, with thigh high boots, triple goddess crown. Bow and quiver of arrows slung over her back was hardly an amazon outfit...but...she was the Goddess of the Amazons and it was made of leather. She watched the amazons celebrate ths night. Her eyes flickering to the impaled traitors,a smile on her lips. kay, so she did not agree with the Lesvos methods, but it was tradition and Velaska was holding up tradition. She felt the presence of the Lioness and looked at where she felt he renergy, she noticed the two glowing golden eyes , an nodded in its direction.~ <p>~ The Silver Goddess~<br>
