<br>
Slowely, the lioness began to walk towards the Goddess.  As she did, Sin slowely shifted into her human form.  Unlike the amazons and the Goddess, Sin's skin clothing was furs of the spotted kind.  The lioness in her loved to hunt the leapard and cheatah...and her clothing showed it.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings, great Artemis,&quot;  Sin spoke in a low sultry voice, much like one would expect a prowling lioness.  She slightly bent her head down in respect, red tresses falling over her cheeks and then back as she looked into the Goddess's eyes.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uardynothewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ardyn O The Wind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/14/02 6:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/amznpardyn/images/julianne1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PARTY</span><hr size=1> Ardyn was dressed in her brown Amazon leathers and shaman headdress adorning her head, sword strapped to her back, spear in her hand, and sais tucked neatly in her boots. She made her way over to the fire. She quirked a brow at the mutilated bodies and sighed as she saw Gabby puking her guts out.<br>
<br>
Poor Gabby didn't have Xena to comfort her, as everyone knew Gabby was Amazon but never had a strong stomach.<br>
<br>
Trailing behind Ardyn was Aja the tiger given to her by her mother Tyger. The stripped black and orange tiger paded behind it's master as she gathered with the tribe.<br>
<br>
She sat down meditation form before the flames and began chanting and painting her face with protective paint and spreading the paint around the bodies to keep their souls from entering her and her athelfi.<br>
<br>
After the short ritual she moved about the group and started mingling with her sisters. <p>~Ardyn O The Wind~<BR> =¤= Amazon Goddess of Virtue =¤=<BR>=ll= Re-Incarnation of the Warrior Shaman Otere=ll=<BR> "What we do in Life echoes in eternity."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udaughterofshylock.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daughter of Shylock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/15/02 5:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PARTY</span><hr size=1> To much surprise, Alysia-Samsara remained a bit quiet as she approached the other amazons. She had in fact destroyed Hope with a single dagger and yet the one who should celebrate the most . . . was silent.<br>
<br>
She refused to cleanse the blood from her hands. Scynthian/Tretmolec ways were becoming more and more clear to the Nation as well to the Queen herself. Death was not taken lightly . . .  especially if taken for the Nation. And Alysia had done just that. She followed Hope, threatened Hope, and with the last bit of Mercy Alysia knew from Eli's teachings leaving her mind and heart . . . she killed her.<br>
<br>
She then approached Velaska and nodded a slight bow in her honor seeing she was indeed Queen of these lands. She then turned and looked over at the body of Hope.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you don't mind Velaska, I wish to take a vile or two of her blood back to Scynthia. One to study, the other to symbolize to enemies of my own, that I am not to be delt with lightly.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked down to two viles in her hand. <br>
<br>
Her senses were well about her as she cast her eyes towards Artemis and Sin. Though she herself was an Ancient and only worshipped that of Gaia in any Goddess form . . . she knew that Artemis and Hera protected the Amazons greatly. She gave a nod of respect to them both and her eyes spoke loudly to them saying: For as long as I shall live, I will protect them all.<br>
